# Copy to `.env.test` at repo root and/or `backend/.env.test` (gitignored).
# Pytest loads repo `.env` then `backend/.env`, then `.env.test` files with **override=True**
# (see `backend/tests/conftest.py`) so integration tests hit a dedicated DB, not your manual dev DB.
#
# Database name must look like a test DB (e.g. include `test`, `-test`, `pytest`, `_test`) or appear in
# DINAMIC_PYTEST_SQLSERVER_DATABASE_ALLOWLIST — see `src/env_settings/sqlserver_pytest_policy.py`.

# SQLSERVER_CONNECTION_STRING=DRIVER={ODBC Driver 18 for SQL Server};SERVER=127.0.0.1,1433;DATABASE=dinamic_inventory_test;UID=...;PWD=...;TrustServerCertificate=yes

# Or split variables (same resolution order as the app; connection string wins if both are set):
# SQLSERVER_SERVER=127.0.0.1,1433
# SQLSERVER_DATABASE=dinamic_inventory_test
# SQLSERVER_UID=sa
# SQLSERVER_PWD=...
# SQLSERVER_DRIVER=ODBC Driver 18 for SQL Server

# Disable automatic wipe between integration tests (rare): DINAMIC_PYTEST_DISABLE_SQLSERVER_TEST_CLEANUP=1

# Pytest also defaults INTERNAL_OCR_PROCESSING_ENABLED=true when unset (see tests/conftest.py),
# because SYSTEM_DEFAULT identification mode is INTERNAL_OCR and CI has no developer .env.

# ---
# Local manual cleanup script (`backend/scripts/clean_local_business_data.py`) loads **only**
# `.env` + `backend/.env` — not `.env.test`. Use `--use-env-test` if you intentionally want test vars.
